    <abstract>
      <t>This memo discusses possible modifications of TLS 1.3, aimed to allow
   trasferring data larger than 64 Kbytes in handshake messages.  One
   possible application for this feature is to allow using post-quantum
   Key Encapsulation Method that have large public key or ciphertext
   size (like Classic McEliece).</t>
    </abstract>
